                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340410-208-victim1351 t18340410-208-viclabel1183"></join>. I had known the prisoner about a month in the employ of Mr. Jay, the foreman at Sowter's - I considered he was in the employ of Jay as usual - he came to our yard, and said he had come from Mr. Jay for some nails to go to Aldersgate-street - knowing Mr. Sowter was building there, I gave him between two and three thousand nails to take there, believing Jay had sent him for them.</p>
